race.comment: Ciaron-Maher-trained QUEIN STEP (9) brings strong form to resumption and has looked sharp in her two recent short-course trials. Was narrowly beaten fresh two back this track/trip/ level and will get every chance racing forward from the handy gate. She has plenty of scope for improvement. OCTOBER STAR (7) wasted no time getting off the mark delivering here on debut over this trip. Had been well prepared, and the promising type can measure up again. INSIST (4) needed the first-up outing at Kembla Grange. Has plenty in the tank and jumps from the paint. Quick improvement is likely. DON'T DOUBT MERLIN (1) also in the mix. Resumes and has a strong first up record.
